According to bugreport #16625 filed against gcc, mozilla/firefox/thunderbird are known not to build static against gcc 3.3.4. See http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=16625 for further information.

The only way I have been able to build Firefox 1.5beta2 using gcc 3.3.4 is to use the --enable-shared and --disable-static configure options. 

For those who are using gcc-g++ 3.3.4, it might be helpful to mention the linking issue as noted at gnu.gcc.org in the build documentation.
